AB  - This paper examines the costs to society when prolonged unemployment of resources occurs following trade liberalization. Clearly such costs could be of sufficient magnitude to outweigh the benefits of a move towards freer trade. The paper analyze the characteristics of a sample of trade-displaced workers, and from this analysis the costs of trade liberalization is a displaced worker and to society are estimated.
